parameters:
Mage Relm: Geniuses are lonely! History has proven that with
great figures!

Mage Relm: Challenging the goblins is my selfishness. It's
okay for both of you to go back.
Mage Relm: Or... would you come with me?

Mage Relm: You're very diligent. Is it because it's a
request?
Clea: No, I've also been made fun of for a long time.

Clea: It's unbelievable to think that my parents were killed
by non-existent dragons.
Clea: Chasing after dragons is proof of going crazy.
Mage Relm: Huh, dragons. Clea-san too?

Clea: It's not just me, Nora-san is also chasing after
dragons.
Thief Nora: Ah, I've also been made fun of! I'm used to it!

Clea: Everyone's goal is to defeat dragons, so we can't back
down against mere goblins.

Clea: It seems like everyone has noticed over here. Please
prepare for battle, everyone!
Thief Nora: Yes, I'm scared, but I'll do my best!
Mage Relm: The same goal as me...

Mage Relm: Hehe! I'll show you the fighting prowess of this
genius!

Relm had obtained three things through her adventure
involving medicinal herbs. One of them was the medicinal
herb, which is the material for the magic book. This was the
original purpose and something that should naturally be
obtained.

It was a coincidence, but they were individuals with the
same foolish goal. They were comrades who chased after the
monster known as dragons, which were considered to be mere
fantasies.

At the end, although they didn't realize it at that time,
they were friends who could speak on equal terms with each
other. And that was what Relm desired the most, deep down.

I had never experienced being trusted and needed to this
extent before. Not as the mage Relm, but as just Relm. It
was a warm and gentle feeling, mixed with ticklishness and
embarrassment.

Dreams freed me from a small room. Dreams blossomed my
talents and brought me a lot of knowledge. Dreams brought
not only companions but also friends to me.

Dreams are what humans need. Dreams are something brilliant,
precious, and recognized and blessed by everyone. Relm has
come this far to prove that.
To prove the value and meaning of dreams.

Mage Relm: Please look! That's the herb I've been searching
for!
Mage Relm: H-Hey, what are you doing!?
Clea: Please be quiet... I can hear something.

Thief Nora: G-Goblins!? I can't believe they actually showed
up... Let's run away quickly!

Clea: I think it would be better for us to evacuate as well.
It's more certain after those goblins leave.

Mage Relm: There's no guarantee that those goblins will
disappear! Besides... I have something I need to do.

Mage Relm: There are things I must retrieve, things I must
pursue...!

Mage Relm: I can't stop here, I need to face even a dragon
if necessary!

Mage Relm: In the ancient book of Subma, the ancestor of
mages, there is a description of how to create a grimoire
that seals demons.

Mage Relm: The herbs here are also one of the ingredients,
but the most important ones are the bones and skin of a
dragon.

Mage Relm: It's okay if you laugh, my dreams have always
been laughed at anyway.

Mage Relm: Geniuses are lonely! History has proven that with
great figures!

Mage Relm: Challenging the goblins is my selfishness. You
two can go back, it's fine.
Mage Relm: Or... would you come with me?
Shall we head to the deepest part of the cave?
Mage Relm: You're so diligent. Is it because it's a request?
Clea: No, I've always been made fun of.

Clea: I can't believe the story about having my parents
killed by non-existent dragons.
Clea: Chasing after dragons is proof of going crazy.
Mage Relm: Huh, dragons? Clea-san too?

Clea: It's not just me, Nora-san is also chasing after
dragons.
Thief Nora: Ah, I've also been made fun of! I'm used to it!

Clea: Everyone's goal is to defeat dragons, but we can't
even handle goblins.

Clea: It seems like everyone has noticed over here. Please
prepare for battle!
Thief Nora: Yes, I'm scared, but I'll do my best!
Mage Relm: The same goal as me...

Mage Relm: Hehe! I'll show you the fighting prowess of this
genius!

Mage Relm: Ugh... strong... everyone except me is
unconscious... damn it

Mage Relm (If we can just keep going like this, maybe we can
escape...)

Mage Relm (It doesn't seem like I'm living up to being a
genius... I won't miss the chance to make friends in the
search for dragons!)

Mage Relm: Come on, you monster! This genius mage will be
your opponent!!
Do you want to skip the adult scene?

Do you want to restart the battle? If you choose No, it will
result in a game over.
Clea: Alright, this should work on the goblins too...!

Mage Relm: Huff... huff... That was tough. If only my powers
weren't sealed, it would have been easier.
Mage Relm: Now, let's collect the herbs--
Thief Nora: E-Everyone! Let's move away from here!
Thief Nora: T-The goblin is calling for reinforcements!
Mage Relm: Huh, we still need to collect the herbs!?

Clea: It would be bad if they come in a group. It's
frustrating, but let's turn back to the village.
Mage Relm: Ugh, even though we fought so hard...!
Mage Relm: Ugh, fine! Let's go back to regroup and recover!
